Stepping Out: The Very Best of Joe Jackson is a compilation album from the English
singer-songwriter, Joe Jackson. The songs, arranged in chronological order, are
taken from nine of his first twelve albums, all of which were released on the A&M
label. Stepping Out: The Very Best of Joe Jackson reached No. 7 in the UK Albums
Chart in October 1990. By this time Jackson had parted company with A&M, with his
next few releases being on the Virgin Records label
